<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>tough cookie • tough cookies</xh5><p> <i>tough cookie</i>—(sl.) an unyielding person who is difficult to deal with: He’s a real <u>tough cookie</u> and you know it.</p><p> <i>tough cookies</i>—(sl., parenthetical) too bad; very unfortunate <i>(also: tough bananas): </i>If you give the wrong answer, well, <u>tough cookies</u>, you have to move backward.</p> </entry>
